data.text:
Here we have a gorgeous and ULTRA RARE vintage original 1930s brown leather National Benzole Mixture key-ring / fob with a chrome / enamel logo. The National Benzole company was a petrol company like British Petroleum and Shell, National Benzole Mixture however, was marketed strongly at the sports and racing driver. In the 1920s and 1930s their mixture was also used in British racing and land speed records. Their advertising was seen on the Brooklands race track in Weybridge and other British racing venues of the period. This awesome key-ring will be a magnificent addition to your 1930s sports or racing car! This over 40 years old key ring has seen light use and it is in excellent original condition! A highly desirable and highly collectible period original key-ring! Most of the key-rings from this period have worn completely or have perished altogether… “Enjoy the Ride!”
